P0.2 Auto-Teardown Implementation Notes:

Files modified:
- internal/providers/aws.go: Added public Teardown(ctx, deploymentID) method
- internal/providers/provider.go: Added TeardownProvider interface and GetAWSProvider() helper
- internal/main.go: Wired TeardownCallback to call awsProvider.Teardown()
- internal/providers/aws_test.go: Added tests for new functionality

Key changes:
1. AWSProvider now exposes Teardown() which wraps the internal teardown() tool
2. TeardownProvider interface enables type-safe teardown capability checking
3. main.go creates awsProvider early and passes it to the teardown callback
4. When cost monitor detects budget exceeded, it now calls actual AWS teardown

Security impact:
- Before: Users enabled auto-teardown but deployments kept running (false sense of security)
- After: Over-budget deployments are actually torn down, preventing cost overruns

Test coverage:
- TestPublicTeardown: Verifies Teardown method is callable
- TestTeardownProvider_Interface: Verifies interface compliance
- TestGetAWSProvider: Verifies helper function
